{"model": "DeepSeek R1-0528 Qwen3 8B", "runtime": "llamacpp", "prompt_name": "code_is_palindrome__t2_tdd", "prompt_tokens": 0, "generation_tokens": 0, "prompt_tps": 375.8, "generation_tps": 73.3, "peak_memory_gb": 0.0, "wall_time_sec": 11.3, "output": "To solve this problem, we need to determine if a given string is a palindrome. A palindrome reads the same forwards and backwards, ignoring spaces, punctuation, and capitalization. The solution involves preprocessing the string to remove non-alphanumeric characters and convert all characters to lowercase, then checking if the resulting string is equal to its reverse.", "error": null, "prompt_hash": "cff7669d8a80"}
{"model": "DeepSeek R1-0528 Qwen3 8B", "runtime": "llamacpp", "prompt_name": "code_lru_cache__t3_direct", "prompt_tokens": 0, "generation_tokens": 0, "prompt_tps": 392.6, "generation_tps": 67.0, "peak_memory_gb": 0.0, "wall_time_sec": 98.3, "output": "def LRUCache(capacity):\n    class Node:\n        __slots__ = ('prev', 'next', 'key', 'value')\n        def __init__(self, key, value):\n            self.key = key\n            self.value = value\n            self.prev = None\n            self.next = None\n\n    head = Node(None, None)\n    tail = Node(None, None)\n    head.next = tail\n    tail.prev = head\n    cache = {}\n    size = 0\n\n    def remove_node(node):\n        nonlocal head, tail\n        node.prev.next = node.next\n        node.next.prev = node.prev\n\n    def add_node_to_head(node):\n        nonlocal head, tail\n        node.prev = head\n        node.next = head.next\n        head.next.prev = node\n        head.next = node\n\n    def get(key):\n        if key in cache:\n            node = cache[key]\n            remove_node(node)\n            add_node_to_head(node)\n            return node.value\n        else:\n            return -1\n\n    def put(key, value):\n        nonlocal cache, size\n        if key in cache:\n            node = cache[key]\n            node.value = value\n            remove_node(node)\n            add_node_to_head(node)\n        else:\n            if size >= capacity:\n                # Remove LRU node (tail.prev)\n                lru_node = tail.prev\n                remove_node(lru_node)\n                del cache[lru_node.key]\n            new_node = Node(key, value)\n            cache[key] = new_node\n            add_node_to_head(new_node)\n            size += 1\n\n    return {\n        'get': get,\n        'put': put\n    }", "error": null, "prompt_hash": "e594f8996a66"}
{"model": "DeepSeek R1-0528 Qwen3 8B", "runtime": "llamacpp", "prompt_name": "code_matrix_rotate__t3_direct", "prompt_tokens": 0, "generation_tokens": 0, "prompt_tps": 247.6, "generation_tps": 73.4, "peak_memory_gb": 0.0, "wall_time_sec": 11.3, "output": "def rotate_90(matrix: list[list[int]]) -> list[list[int]]:\n    n = len(matrix)\n    # Create a new matrix with zeros, same size as input\n    rotated = [[0] * n for _ in range(n)]\n    # Iterate over each element and place it in the rotated matrix\n    for i in range(n):\n        for j in range(n):\n            rotated[j][n-1-i] = matrix[i][j]\n    return rotated", "error": null, "prompt_hash": "423335f26fd2"}
