{"model": "DeepSeek R1-0528 Qwen3 8B", "runtime": "llamacpp", "prompt_name": "math_combinatorics__t3_cot", "prompt_tokens": 0, "generation_tokens": 0, "prompt_tps": 232.3, "generation_tps": 69.9, "peak_memory_gb": 0.0, "wall_time_sec": 59.7, "output": "The problem involves finding the number of ways to choose 3 items from a set of 7, which is a combination problem where the order of selection does not matter.\n\nThe combination formula is C(n, k) = n! / (k! * (n - k)!) , where n is the total number of items and k is the number to choose.\n\nHere, n = 7 and k = 3.\n\nC(7, 3) = 7! / (3! * 4!) = (7 \u00d7 6 \u00d7 5 \u00d7 4!) / (3! \u00d7 4!) = (7 \u00d7 6 \u00d7 5) / (6) because 3! = 6 and the 4! terms cancel.\n\n(7 \u00d7 6 \u00d7 5) / 6 = 7 \u00d7 5 = 35.\n\nAlternatively, using the binomial coefficient directly, C(7, 3) = 35.\n\nANSWER: 35", "error": null, "prompt_hash": "0906c375ac54"}
